(Note: RDFS, or RDF Schema, is a vocabulary for describing RDF triples and defining classes and properties in the Resource Description Framework (RDF), which is a standard model for data interchange on the Web. OWL, or Web Ontology Language, is a language for defining and instantiating web ontologies, which are formal representations of knowledge in a specific domain.)
